<title>How to enable and disable Driver Verifier in Windows 10 [Tip]</title>
<link>https://dottech.org/204967/how-to-enable-and-disable-driver-verifier-in-windows-10/</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >https://dottech.org/204967/how-to-enable-and-disable-driver-verifier-in-windows-10/</guid>
<description>&lt;p&gt;One of the diagnostic tools that is built into Windows 10 is the Driver Verifier. The Driver Verifier verifies Microsoft drivers as well as third-party drivers. The way the verification process works is an interesting one. Windows puts drivers to the test by putting them through heavy stress with the intention of making drivers that are incompatible, outdated, or not good enough fail on purpose so that they can be identified and thus the right ones verified.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;ins class=&quot;adsbygoogle&quot; data-ad-format=&quot;fluid&quot; data-ad-layout=&quot;in-article&quot; data-ad-client=&quot;ca-pub-9004832441082633&quot; data-ad-slot=&quot;4488607600&quot;/&gt; &amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;When you get a driver that doesn’t pass the test, the BSoD (Blue Screen of Death) appears on the computer’s display. The DSoD then creates a crash dump so that it can be debugged.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;h3&gt;How to run Driver Verifier&lt;/h3&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;There are a few ways you can get the Verifier open. It doesn’t matter which way you do it. Those wanting to do it from the search field in the taskbar can type “Verifier” and then click on the “Verifier Run command” to get it open.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-Run-command.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-full wp-image-204968 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-Run-command.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;391&quot; height=&quot;680&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-Run-command.jpg?200 391w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-Run-command-144x250.jpg?200 144w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-Run-command-173x300.jpg?200 173w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-Run-command-70x122.jpg?200 70w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 391px) 100vw, 391px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;You can also open the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dottech.org/203896/how-to-change-command-prompt-to-admin-and-pin-it-to-taskbar-in-windows-10/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;Command Prompt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and type “Verifier” and press the Enter key on your keyboards to run it.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204969 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt-620x324.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;324&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt-620x324.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt-250x131.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt-768x402.jpg?200 768w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt-300x157.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt-70x37.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-command-prompt.jpg?200 979w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Lastly, you can open Task Manager, create a new task and then choose to open the Verifier. To do that, click on “File” and then “Run new task.”&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204970 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task-620x376.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;376&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task-620x376.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task-250x152.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task-768x466.jpg?200 768w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task-300x182.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task-70x42.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Run-new-task.jpg?200 838w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Then type “Verifier” into the available field before clicking on the “OK” button.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204971 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-task-620x452.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;452&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-task-620x452.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-task-250x182.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-task-300x219.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-task-70x51.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Verifier-task.jpg?200 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;The Verifier is now open.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;h3&gt;How to Configure Driver Verifier Settings&lt;/h3&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Now that you have opened the Verifier, you then need to configure its settings and enable it, so it is working. To get started on that, select the “Create custom settings (for code developers)” option and then click on the “Next” button at the bottom.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204972 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings-620x512.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;512&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings-620x512.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings-250x206.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings-300x248.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings-70x58.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Create-custom-settings.jpg?200 637w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;ins class=&quot;adsbygoogle&quot; data-ad-client=&quot;ca-pub-9004832441082633&quot; data-ad-slot=&quot;6591595958&quot; data-ad-format=&quot;auto&quot;/&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Place the checkmark in the “Select driver names from a list” option and then click on the “Next” button once again.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204976 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names-620x512.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;512&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names-620x512.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names-250x206.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names-300x248.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names-70x58.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Select-driver-names.jpg?200 637w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Checkmark the checkboxes next to “I/O verification,” “Force pending I/O requests” and “IRP Logging” and then click on the “Next” button.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204973 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager-620x512.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;512&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager-620x512.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager-250x206.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager-300x248.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager-70x58.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Driver-verifier-manager.jpg?200 637w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;You now need to go through the list and check all the boxes for drivers that are not provided by Microsoft. You can easily tell which ones those are by looking in the “Provider” column. (Don’t forget to scroll down the screen so you can see them all.)&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204975 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft-620x512.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;512&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft-620x512.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft-250x206.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft-300x248.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft-70x58.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Non-Microsoft.jpg?200 637w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Click on the “Finish” button when you get to the bottom of the list.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204974 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish-620x512.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;512&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish-620x512.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish-250x206.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish-300x248.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish-70x58.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Finish.jpg?200 637w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;h3&gt;How to Disable Driver Verifier&lt;/h3&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;When you want to turn off the Driver Verifier, you just run it again as you did at the beginning of the guide (either from the search, Command Prompt or Task Manager), and then select the “Delete existing settings” from the menu. When you click on the “Finish” button, it is then disabled.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings.jpg?200&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-204979 colorbox-204967&quot; src=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings-620x512.jpg?200&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;620&quot; height=&quot;512&quot; srcset=&quot;https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings-620x512.jpg?200 620w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings-250x206.jpg?200 250w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings-300x248.jpg?200 300w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings-70x58.jpg?200 70w, https://dt.azadicdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Delete-existing-settings.jpg?200 637w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Most of us technology enthusiasts who use computers regularly will need to go about installing a third-party driver every once in a while, and we often assume those drivers are going to be in perfect working order without thinking a second thought about it. The Driver Verifier tool which is available in all versions of Windows 10 is like your driver police, designed to keep all of those third-party drivers in check so your operating system is always working as best as it can.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;div class=&quot;ads&quot;&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;h3&gt;Related Posts&lt;/h3&gt;&amp;#13;
